title: Senior Attorney
description: Intelligence Law: Advise NSA's Tailored Access Operations on computer network exploitation Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) activities to ensure that critical national intelligence requirements are carried out in compliance with applicable law and policy. Coordinate with Department of Justice, Federal Bureau of Investigation, Department of Defense, and other intelligence community members to resolve intergovernmental concerns and ensure that joint operations are conducted effectively and within each participant's area of legal authority. Information Assurance/Cyber Security Law: Advised NSA's Threat Operations Center (NTOC) on computer network defense activities. Reviewed proposed NTOC projects and participated in operational planning to enable NTOC to respond to cyber threats against Department of Defense and national security system networks while remaining in compliance with applicable law and policy. Drafted and negotiated agreements between NTOC and other U.S. Government entities. Provided emergency after-hours legal reviews and advice in crisis situations. Chosen by NTOC senior leadership to be the only attorney included with the NTOC group that received the 2011 Director's Team Excellence Award, given to honor the efforts of three major NSA organizations that worked together to achieve full operational capability of the technology that is instrumental to the continued success of NSA's computer network defense mission. Served on the interagency team that worked through complex legal and policy issues to enable the successful launch of the pilot for the Defense Industrial Base (DIB) Enhanced Cybersecurity Services (DECS) program, a joint Department of Defense/Department of Homeland Security initiative via which NSA provides classified cyber threat information to participating Internet service providers to enable the ISPs to provide more effective network security services to their DIB customers.

title: Intelligence /Global Network Analyst/Team Chief
description: -Digital Network Lead Analyst/Tailored Access Operations Liaison in the Signals Intelligence Directorate since April 2008. Team chief since June 2009. Led efforts to utilize new skills and tools to achieve high priority objectives. -Direct and manage information and workflow throughout the team to ensure timelessness of reporting, including monitoring the criteria for the selection of reportable intelligence. -Spearheaded planning the future development of targets; provided guidance and leadership for organizational changes and challenges. Served as key facilitator of communication within the team as a spokesperson for the team and branch. -Interfaced with Intelligence Community components and provided customer support and accurately represented NSA capabilities. -Developed and led Computer Network Operations (CNO) to obtain strategic and actionable foreign intelligence and facilitated network warfare. Directly impacted U.S. national intelligence policy and directives to track and thwart WMD programs. -Subject Matter Expert Reporter on Middle East and North Africa targets, to include fast-paced work environments, worked under strict deadlines as well as advanced analytical assessment reports. Authored, edited, and released SIGINT intelligence reports and assessments to include mentoring several less experienced employees while producing products in accordance with relevant policies and procedures. -Graduate of the Intelligence Analysis Development Program (IADP), a robust three-year training program after completing 800 hours of training and five unique Signals Intelligence tours covering a variety of skills and job junctions to include intelligence reporting, social network analysis, advanced research, signals development, and computer network operations. -Specialization and target expertise in Middle Eastern and Combating Proliferation target sets. -completed training courses in cell technology, Network+ bootamp, TCP/IP Networking as well as a variety of classes.

title: Global Exploitation and Network Vulnerability Analyst
description: Worked in the office of Protocol Exploitation to analyze and exploit various protocols. Extensive protocol knowledge includes VOIP protocols, Chat Protocols and Microsoft Terminal Services based protocols. Reverse Engineered Remote Desktop, an open source program to process Microsoft Terminal Services. Developed modules in C++ to process several protocols. These libraries are integrated into larger systems to form complete processing solutions used agency wide. Teamed with coworkers in creating a project from the ground up to process the enormous quantities of data obtained by the agency. The metadata harvested by the intelligence analysts produces actionable intelligence which forms intelligence reports. Signals Analysis Development Program Developed expertise in various aspects of signals analysis ranging from demodulation to bit level analysis. Worked with several foreign partners, including work conducted overseas to produce intelligence out of specific foreign signals of interest. Created Quick Reaction Capabilities (QRC) against signals of high priority to the agency. This included the use of scripting and other programming in order to rapidly produce a product capable of processing these signals. Toured in Tailored Access Operations to work specific projects regarding Computer Network Exploitation (CNE) of Microsoft Windows based machines.

title: Global Exploitation and Network Vulnerability Analyst
description: Worked in the office of Protocol Exploitation to analyze and exploit various protocols. Extensive protocol knowledge includes VOIP protocols, Chat Protocols and Microsoft Terminal Services based protocols. Reverse Engineered Remote Desktop, an open source program to process Microsoft Terminal Services. Developed modules in C++ to process several protocols. These libraries are integrated into larger systems to form complete processing solutions used agency wide. Teamed with coworkers in creating a project from the ground up to process the enormous quantities of data obtained by the agency. The metadata harvested by the intelligence analysts produces actionable intelligence which forms intelligence reports. Signals Analysis Development Program Developed expertise in various aspects of signals analysis ranging from demodulation to bit level analysis. Worked with several foreign partners, including work conducted overseas to produce intelligence out of specific foreign signals of interest. Created Quick Reaction Capabilities (QRC) against signals of high priority to the agency. This included the use of scripting and other programming in order to rapidly produce a product capable of processing these signals. Toured in Tailored Access Operations to work specific projects regarding Computer Network Exploitation (CNE) of Microsoft Windows based machines.

title: Intelligence /Global Network Analyst/Team Chief
description: -Digital Network Lead Analyst/Tailored Access Operations Liaison in the Signals Intelligence Directorate since April 2008. Team chief since June 2009. Led efforts to utilize new skills and tools to achieve high priority objectives. -Direct and manage information and workflow throughout the team to ensure timelessness of reporting, including monitoring the criteria for the selection of reportable intelligence. -Spearheaded planning the future development of targets; provided guidance and leadership for organizational changes and challenges. Served as key facilitator of communication within the team as a spokesperson for the team and branch. -Interfaced with Intelligence Community components and provided customer support and accurately represented NSA capabilities. -Developed and led Computer Network Operations (CNO) to obtain strategic and actionable foreign intelligence and facilitated network warfare. Directly impacted U.S. national intelligence policy and directives to track and thwart WMD programs. -Subject Matter Expert Reporter on Middle East and North Africa targets, to include fast-paced work environments, worked under strict deadlines as well as advanced analytical assessment reports. Authored, edited, and released SIGINT intelligence reports and assessments to include mentoring several less experienced employees while producing products in accordance with relevant policies and procedures. -Graduate of the Intelligence Analysis Development Program (IADP), a robust three-year training program after completing 800 hours of training and five unique Signals Intelligence tours covering a variety of skills and job junctions to include intelligence reporting, social network analysis, advanced research, signals development, and computer network operations. -Specialization and target expertise in Middle Eastern and Combating Proliferation target sets. -completed training courses in cell technology, Network+ bootamp, TCP/IP Networking as well as a variety of classes.
